comments.body:
You can do this by painting the picture with a color filter:

```csharp
using (var paint = new SKPaint()) {
    paint.ColorFilter = SKColorFilter.CreateXferMode(SKColors.Red, SKXferMode.SrcIn);
    canvas.DrawPicture(svg.Picture, paint);
}
```

(You can re-open the issue if this is not the result that you are looking for.)

This works great for Android, but doesn't work on Desktop for me. Or the newer
paint.ColorFilter = SKColorFilter.CreateBlendMode(SKColor.Red, SKBlendMode.SrcIn);
I'm using an fa.solid SVG.
